        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 8:39PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 839 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles east of Biddle, or 36 miles southeast of Broadus, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ridge.
</description>
